parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Sun Shell Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission due to sun shell failure can cause the vehicle to jerk, bog down, or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to potential accidents or loss of control, especially when merging onto busy highways.
symptoms: The transmission jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the transmission fails to engage into gear (particularly 1st to 2nd or 3rd to 4th)
the vehicle has trouble reversing
the transmission leaks fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Front Pump Cover Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front pump cover can cause the transmission to fail, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks if the vehicle loses power or control while in motion.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks from the front pump cover
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the vehicle has difficulty shifting gears
the transmission needs to be replaced or rebuilt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty mass air flow sensor can cause the engine to stall or cut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or cuts off while driving
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An oil leak can cause engine damage, leading to premature wear and potentially catastrophic failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil is leaking from the vehicle
the oil level needs to be refilled frequently
the engine is making unusual noises or smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty ABS system can cause the vehicle to fail to stop or slow down, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when approaching intersections or stop signs.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle fails to stop or slow down
the vehicle continues to move despite pressing the brakes
the brakes engage and disengage erratically
the vehicle experiences a loss of brake function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop, leading to potential rear-end collisions.
symptoms: Brake lights do not illuminate when the brake pedal is depressed
inability to replace brake light bulbs due to malfunctioning tailgate actuator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning tailgate actuator can prevent the tailgate from opening properly, making it difficult to access the cargo area and potentially causing inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Tailgate does not open properly
inability to replace brake light bulbs due to malfunctioning tailgate actuator.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of serious injury or fatality to occupants, as they are not provided with the necessary protection to mitigate the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a frontal impact
despite the severity of the crash meeting the deployment threshold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of trailer control can lead to accidents, damage to property, and injury or fatality to occupants, as the trailer can swing out of control and collide with other vehicles or objects.
symptoms: Trailer fishtails or swings out of control while driving
especially when going down hills or in inclement weather.
